## Semantic Colors

DaisyUI uses semantic color names that adapt to themes:

```erb
<%# Base colors %>
<p class="text-base-content">Regular text</p>
<p class="bg-base-100">Background</p>

<%# Semantic colors %>
<p class="text-primary">Primary accent</p>
<p class="text-error">Error message</p>
<p class="text-success">Success message</p>
```

Always prefer semantic colors over hardcoded values for theme compatibility.
